            "uid": "33525"
          },
          "date": "2023-02-17",
          "content": "According to Fraser Institute, Canadians spend an average of $5,789 annually on taxes for health care coverage. This is significantly lower than the $10,000 that each American spends on average. Your income determines how much you pay in taxes. People who have higher incomes pay more in taxes, which helps fund health care for families who earn less.\n你的Medicare是别人税金在付的。别觉得免费医保真的是免费的，多赚点钱多交点税回馈社会。"
        }
